docs.lead_paragraph: ST. PETERSBURG, Fla., Feb. 16 (AP)--Louise Suggs sank a 10foot putt on the eighteenth green for a birdie 3 today. The shot enabled the Sea Island, Ga., player to tie Betty Jameson for the lead after 54 holes of the $5,000 St. Petersburg women's open golf tournament.

headline.main: Louise Suggs and Betty Jameson Tie for Lead in St. Petersburg Open Golf; GEORGIAN TALLIES 69 FOR 210 TOTAL Miss Suggs Draws Even With Betty Jameson, Who Posts 70 for Third Round
